NBA ALL-STAR WEEKEND
February 12, 2010
Amar'e Stoudemire
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT
 
 
  
 
  
  
   
  Q. If you were a GM, who would be your starting five?  
 AMARE STOUDEMIRE: All-time or --  
  
  Q. Right now, you're the general manager of your team.   
 AMARE STOUDEMIRE: Starting at center I'll go with Dwight Howard. Starting at forward I'd probably go with Tim Duncan. Starting at small forward, probably LeBron James. Two guards, Kobe Bryant, at the point Steve Nash.  
  
  Q. Who is the NBA's entertainer right now, fun to watch?  
 AMARE STOUDEMIRE: Best entertainer, basketball?   
  
  Q. Mm-hmm.   
 AMARE STOUDEMIRE: LeBron James. I love watching LeBron James.  
  
  Q. Who is the most underrated NBA player right now who's not getting the attention, the respect?  
  
  Q. What's your favorite city to visit and why?  
 AMARE STOUDEMIRE: Probably Orlando, the reason being that's my hometown.   
   
  End of FastScripts  
  
  
  

END_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT